MATERI 1: PARTS OF SPEECH (Kelas Kata)
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Perkiraan waktu belajar: 3-4 hari
Kaitan TOEIC: Dasar semua soal Part 5 (Word Form questions)

APA ITU PARTS OF SPEECH?
Bayangkan kalimat bahasa Inggris seperti tim sepak bola. Setiap pemain punya peran berbeda.
Parts of speech adalah PERAN dari setiap kata dalam kalimat.
Ada 8 jenis kelas kata. Kamu WAJIB hafal semuanya.

─────────────────────────────────────────────
1. NOUN (Kata Benda)
─────────────────────────────────────────────
→ Apa itu: Kata yang menyebut orang, tempat, benda, atau ide
→ Pertanyaan kunci: "Apa?" atau "Siapa?"

Jenis-jenis Noun:
   a) Common Noun = benda umum
      Contoh: book, computer, office, meeting, project

   b) Proper Noun = nama khusus (selalu huruf kapital)
      Contoh: Google, Jakarta, Monday, John

   c) Abstract Noun = tidak bisa dilihat/disentuh, tapi dirasakan
      Contoh: happiness (kebahagiaan), success (kesuksesan), information (informasi)

   d) Collective Noun = kelompok
      Contoh: team (tim), staff (staf), committee (panitia)

Contoh kalimat:
   - The programmer fixed the bug. (programmer = noun, bug = noun)
   - The meeting will start at 9 AM. (meeting = noun)
   - Our team finished the project on time. (team = noun, project = noun)

Tanda-tanda sebuah kata adalah NOUN:
   - Bisa ditambah "a/an/the" di depannya
   - Bisa dijamakkan dengan -s/-es
   - Sering ada akhiran: -tion, -ness, -ment, -ity, -er, -or

Contoh akhiran noun: information, happiness, management, ability, teacher, director

─────────────────────────────────────────────
2. VERB (Kata Kerja)
─────────────────────────────────────────────
→ Apa itu: Kata yang menyatakan aksi, kejadian, atau keadaan
→ Pertanyaan kunci: "Apa yang dilakukan?"

Jenis Verb:
   a) Action Verb = kata kerja aksi nyata
      Contoh: run, write, send, develop, install, debug, present

   b) Linking Verb = kata kerja penghubung (menghubungkan subjek ke deskripsinya)
      Contoh: is, are, was, were, seem, appear, become, feel, look, sound, taste

   c) Auxiliary/Helping Verb = kata kerja bantu
      Contoh: do, does, did, will, shall, can, could, may, might, must, should, would, have, has, had

Contoh kalimat:
   - She develops mobile applications. (develops = action verb)
   - The system is running correctly. (is = linking verb, running = action verb)
   - You should update the software. (should = auxiliary, update = action verb)

Bentuk-bentuk Verb yang wajib kamu tahu:
   V1 = Base form (bentuk dasar): write, send, go
   V2 = Past form (masa lalu): wrote, sent, went
   V3 = Past participle: written, sent, gone
   V-ing = Present participle: writing, sending, going

─────────────────────────────────────────────
3. ADJECTIVE (Kata Sifat)
─────────────────────────────────────────────
→ Apa itu: Kata yang menerangkan/mendeskripsikan NOUN
→ Pertanyaan kunci: "Bagaimana?" atau "Yang mana?"

Contoh:
   - a fast computer (fast menerangkan computer)
   - an experienced programmer (experienced menerangkan programmer)
   - The new system is efficient. (new menerangkan system, efficient menerangkan system)

Posisi adjective:
   a) Sebelum noun: a reliable network
   b) Setelah linking verb: The network is reliable.

Akhiran adjective yang umum:
   -ful (careful, useful, helpful)
   -less (careless, useless, wireless)
   -ous (famous, dangerous, serious)
   -able/-ible (reliable, flexible, accessible)
   -al (digital, technical, professional)
   -ive (creative, productive, effective)

─────────────────────────────────────────────
4. ADVERB (Kata Keterangan)
─────────────────────────────────────────────
→ Apa itu: Kata yang menerangkan VERB, ADJECTIVE, atau ADVERB lain
→ Pertanyaan kunci: "Bagaimana?", "Kapan?", "Di mana?", "Seberapa?"

Jenis Adverb:
   a) Manner (cara): quickly, carefully, efficiently, professionally
   b) Time (waktu): now, yesterday, soon, already, still
   c) Frequency (frekuensi): always, usually, often, sometimes, rarely, never
   d) Place (tempat): here, there, everywhere, outside
   e) Degree (tingkat): very, quite, extremely, too, enough

Contoh kalimat:
   - She types quickly. (quickly menerangkan verba "types")
   - The server is extremely slow today. (extremely menerangkan adjective "slow")
   - He always arrives on time. (always menerangkan verba "arrives")

Rumus umum: Adjective + -ly = Adverb
   quick → quickly
   careful → carefully
   professional → professionally
   PENGECUALIAN: good → well (bukan "goodly")

─────────────────────────────────────────────
5. PRONOUN (Kata Ganti)
─────────────────────────────────────────────
→ Apa itu: Kata yang menggantikan noun agar kalimat tidak berulang

Jenis Pronoun — WAJIB HAFAL:

   Subject Pronoun (posisi sebagai subjek kalimat):
   I, you, he, she, it, we, they
   → I work in IT. / She manages the team. / They finished the project.

   Object Pronoun (posisi sebagai objek):
   me, you, him, her, it, us, them
   → Please email me. / The manager called him. / We support them.

   Possessive Adjective (menunjukkan kepemilikan, diikuti noun):
   my, your, his, her, its, our, their
   → My computer crashed. / Her password expired. / Our system is updated.

   Possessive Pronoun (menunjukkan kepemilikan, berdiri sendiri tanpa noun):
   mine, yours, his, hers, its, ours, theirs
   → This laptop is mine. / That account is hers. / The problem is theirs.

   Reflexive Pronoun (diri sendiri):
   myself, yourself, himself, herself, itself, ourselves, yourselves, themselves
   → He fixed the bug himself. / The program updated itself.

TOEIC TRAP — Jebakan yang sering keluar:
   ❌ SALAH: The manager and me will attend the meeting.
   ✅ BENAR: The manager and I will attend the meeting.
   (Setelah "and", gunakan Subject Pronoun jika sebagai subjek)

   ❌ SALAH: Please send the report to John and I.
   ✅ BENAR: Please send the report to John and me.
   (Setelah "to", gunakan Object Pronoun)

─────────────────────────────────────────────
6. PREPOSITION (Kata Depan)
─────────────────────────────────────────────
→ Apa itu: Kata yang menunjukkan hubungan antara noun/pronoun dengan bagian kalimat lain
→ Selalu diikuti noun atau pronoun (disebut "object of preposition")

Preposition yang paling sering keluar di TOEIC:
   Waktu: in, on, at, before, after, during, since, for, by, until
   Tempat: in, on, at, under, above, between, among, next to, near
   Arah: to, from, into, out of, toward, through

Rumus penting:
   AT = waktu spesifik (at 9 AM, at noon, at night)
   ON = hari/tanggal (on Monday, on June 5th)
   IN = periode waktu (in the morning, in June, in 2024)

Contoh kalimat:
   - The meeting starts at 10 AM on Monday. 
   - The files are stored in the server.
   - Please submit the report by Friday.
   - During the training, please turn off your phones.

─────────────────────────────────────────────
7. CONJUNCTION (Kata Penghubung)
─────────────────────────────────────────────
→ Apa itu: Kata yang menghubungkan kata, frasa, atau kalimat

Jenis:
   a) Coordinating: and, but, or, so, yet, for, nor
   b) Subordinating: because, although, when, if, while, since, after, before
   c) Correlative: both...and, either...or, neither...nor, not only...but also

Contoh:
   - She is a developer and a designer.
   - The server crashed because of the update.
   - Although the deadline is tight, we will finish it.

─────────────────────────────────────────────
8. INTERJECTION (Kata Seru)
─────────────────────────────────────────────
→ Apa itu: Ekspresi perasaan yang berdiri sendiri
→ Jarang muncul di TOEIC, tapi perlu dikenal
→ Contoh: Wow! Oh! Oops! Great! Well...

