ANALOGI:
Kalimat bahasa Inggris seperti sandwich. Ada lapisan yang wajib ada, ada yang opsional.
Lapisan wajib: ROTI (Subject) + ISI (Verb)
Lapisan tambahan: keju, selada (Object, Complement, Adverb)

─────────────────────────────────────────────
POLA 1: S + V (Subject + Verb)
─────────────────────────────────────────────
→ Kalimat paling sederhana. Hanya subjek dan kata kerja.

S         V
The server crashed.
She resigned.
The meeting ended.
The program runs.
Everyone left.

─────────────────────────────────────────────
POLA 2: S + V + O (Subject + Verb + Object)
─────────────────────────────────────────────
→ Paling umum. Ada yang melakukan aksi (S), aksi itu (V), dan yang terkena aksi (O).
→ Object menjawab pertanyaan "apa?" atau "siapa?" setelah verb

S            V          O
The developer fixed     the bug.
She          sent       an email.
Our team     completed  the project.
He           updated    the software.
Management   approved   the proposal.

─────────────────────────────────────────────
POLA 3: S + V + C (Subject + Verb + Complement)
─────────────────────────────────────────────
→ Digunakan dengan LINKING VERB (is, are, seem, become, feel, look, appear)
→ Complement menerangkan SUBJEK (bukan menerima aksi)

S               V (Linking)    C (Complement)
The system      is             down.
She             became         the team leader.
The results     seem           promising.
The interface   looks          user-friendly.
The deadline    is             next Friday.

BEDAKAN:
   S + V + O: The manager wrote a report. (report = objek, menerima aksi)
   S + V + C: The manager is experienced. (experienced = menerangkan manager)

─────────────────────────────────────────────
POLA 4: S + V + O + O (Indirect Object + Direct Object)
─────────────────────────────────────────────
→ Ada dua objek: indirect object (siapa yang mendapat sesuatu) dan direct object (apa yang diberikan)

S            V       IO (kepada siapa)    DO (apa)
The manager  gave    the team             feedback.
She          sent    me                   the document.
HR           offered  him                  a promotion.
Please       give    the client           a demo.

Bisa juga ditulis dengan "to":
   The manager gave feedback to the team.
   She sent the document to me.

─────────────────────────────────────────────
POLA 5: S + V + O + C (Object + Object Complement)
─────────────────────────────────────────────
→ Complement menerangkan OBJECT (bukan subjek)

S            V          O              C
They         elected    her            team leader.
We           found      the system     unstable.
The update   made       the app        faster.
Management   named      him            project manager.

