MATERI 3: TO BE SYSTEM
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Perkiraan waktu belajar: 3-4 hari
Prasyarat: Materi 1 & 2
Kaitan TOEIC: Dasar passive voice dan semua tense

TO BE adalah kata kerja yang PALING PENTING dalam bahasa Inggris.
Tanpa menguasai to be, kamu tidak bisa memahami passive voice, perfect tense, dll.

TABEL TO BE LENGKAP:

Subjek          Present       Past          Future
I               am            was           will be
You             are           were          will be
He/She/It       is            was           will be
We              are           were          will be
They            are           were          will be

CARA HAFAL:
   Singular present: is (he/she/it) → "dia IS"
   Plural present: are (we/they/you) → "kita ARE"
   I = am (khusus I, satu-satunya)
   Semua past: was (singular) / were (plural)

─────────────────────────────────────────────
KALIMAT POSITIF
─────────────────────────────────────────────
Present:
   I am a programmer.
   She is the project manager.
   They are on a business trip.
   We are ready for the presentation.

Past:
   The server was offline yesterday.
   The meetings were productive.
   I was absent from work last Monday.

Future:
   The deadline will be next Friday.
   The new employees will be trained next week.

─────────────────────────────────────────────
KALIMAT NEGATIF
─────────────────────────────────────────────
Rumus: Subject + To Be + NOT

   I am not available on that day.
   The system is not responding.
   They were not informed about the changes.
   The report will not be ready by tomorrow.

Bentuk singkat (contractions):
   is not = isn't
   are not = aren't
   was not = wasn't
   were not = weren't
   will not be = won't be

─────────────────────────────────────────────
KALIMAT PERTANYAAN (YES/NO QUESTION)
─────────────────────────────────────────────
Rumus: To Be + Subject + ...?

   Is she the team leader?
   Are you available for a meeting?
   Was the project completed on time?
   Were the files backed up?
   Will the system be updated tonight?

JAWABAN SINGKAT:
   Yes, she is. / No, she isn't.
   Yes, I am. / No, I'm not. (INGAT: tidak ada "No, I amn't")
   Yes, it was. / No, it wasn't.

