━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Prasyarat: Materi 3, 4
Kaitan TOEIC: Paling sering keluar di semua Part

KAPAN DIGUNAKAN:
   1. Kebiasaan atau rutinitas (sesuatu yang sering/selalu terjadi)
   2. Fakta umum / kebenaran ilmiah
   3. Jadwal resmi yang sudah pasti
   4. Perasaan dan keadaan saat ini (dengan stative verb)

─────────────────────────────────────────────
RUMUS KALIMAT POSITIF
─────────────────────────────────────────────
   I/You/We/They + V1 (base form)
   He/She/It + V1 + s/es

ATURAN PENAMBAHAN S/ES:
   Kebanyakan verb: tambah -s
      work → works, send → sends, read → reads

   Verb berakhiran -s, -sh, -ch, -x, -z, -o: tambah -es
      teach → teaches, fix → fixes, go → goes, do → does, watch → watches

   Verb berakhiran consonant + -y: ganti -y dengan -ies
      study → studies, carry → carries, apply → applies
   
   PENGECUALIAN: play → plays (karena -ay bukan consonant + y)

Contoh:
   The developer writes code every day.
   She checks her email every morning.
   The server processes thousands of requests per second.
   He manages the database.
   They conduct weekly meetings.

─────────────────────────────────────────────
RUMUS KALIMAT NEGATIF
─────────────────────────────────────────────
   I/You/We/They + DO NOT (DON'T) + V1
   He/She/It + DOES NOT (DOESN'T) + V1

   PENTING: Setelah does/do, verb kembali ke base form (tidak ada -s/-es)
   ❌ She doesn't works here.
   ✅ She doesn't work here.

Contoh:
   The system doesn't support that file format.
   They don't use outdated software.
   He doesn't attend every meeting.
   We don't have enough storage space.

─────────────────────────────────────────────
RUMUS KALIMAT PERTANYAAN
─────────────────────────────────────────────
   DO + I/You/We/They + V1?
   DOES + He/She/It + V1?

Contoh:
   Do you know how to fix this error?
   Does the application run on Android?
   Does she handle the client accounts?
   Do they offer technical support?

─────────────────────────────────────────────
FREQUENCY ADVERBS (Kata Keterangan Frekuensi)
─────────────────────────────────────────────
Urutan dari paling sering ke paling jarang:
   always (100%) → usually (80%) → often (60%) → sometimes (40%) → rarely (20%) → never (0%)

Posisi: SEBELUM verb utama, tapi SETELAH to be
   She always arrives early.
   He is always on time.
   They rarely miss a deadline.
   The system usually updates automatically.

TOEIC TRAP — Posisi frequency adverb:
   ❌ She arrives always early.
   ✅ She always arrives early.

