Kaitan TOEIC: Listening Part 2 — WAJIB sangat kuat

─────────────────────────────────────────────
YES/NO QUESTIONS
─────────────────────────────────────────────
Rumus: Auxiliary/To Be + Subject + Verb?

   Is the server online?
   Are you available for a call?
   Do you have the login credentials?
   Does the software support Mac OS?
   Did you submit the bug report?
   Can you finish this by tomorrow?
   Will the update be released today?

Jawaban singkat:
   Yes, it is. / No, it isn't.
   Yes, I do. / No, I don't.
   Yes, she did. / No, she didn't.

─────────────────────────────────────────────
WH-QUESTIONS (Kata Tanya)
─────────────────────────────────────────────
WHAT = apa
   What is the error message?
   What time does the server go down for maintenance?
   What did you find in the report?

WHERE = di mana
   Where is the backup stored?
   Where can I find the user manual?
   Where did the client go?

WHEN = kapan
   When will the update be released?
   When is the deadline?
   When did the problem start?

WHY = mengapa
   Why is the system slow?
   Why did you change the password?
   Why hasn't the client responded?

WHO = siapa
   Who is responsible for the database?
   Who sent this email?
   Who will attend the meeting?

WHICH = yang mana
   Which version of the software are you using?
   Which department handles this?
   Which option would you prefer?

HOW = bagaimana
   How do I reset my password?
   How does this feature work?
   How did you fix the issue?

HOW LONG = berapa lama
   How long will the maintenance take?
   How long have you worked here?

HOW OFTEN = seberapa sering
   How often do backups run?
   How often does this error occur?

HOW MANY = berapa banyak (untuk countable)
   How many users are online?
   How many bugs were found?

HOW MUCH = berapa banyak (untuk uncountable)
   How much storage is available?
   How much time do we have?

TOEIC LISTENING PART 2 STRATEGY:
   - Dengarkan kata pertama kalimat (siapa? apa? kapan? dll)
   - Jawaban yang benar harus LANGSUNG menjawab pertanyaan itu
   - Hati-hati dengan "jebakan bunyi" — pilihan yang bunyinya mirip tapi maknanya salah

