Kaitan TOEIC: Paling sering keluar, ada di semua Part

─────────────────────────────────────────────
PREPOSISI WAKTU
─────────────────────────────────────────────

AT (waktu spesifik/titik waktu):
   at 9 AM, at noon, at midnight, at the weekend (BrE), at night

ON (hari dan tanggal):
   on Monday, on June 5th, on New Year's Day, on my birthday

IN (periode waktu lebih panjang):
   in the morning/afternoon/evening
   in June, in 2024, in the 21st century
   in three days (setelah tiga hari)

Tabel ringkas:
   AT    →  jam         : at 3 PM
   ON    →  hari/tanggal: on Thursday, on May 10th
   IN    →  bulan/tahun : in April, in 2023

Preposisi waktu lainnya:
   BEFORE = sebelum: Please submit before Friday.
   AFTER = setelah: The meeting is after lunch.
   DURING = selama (bersamaan): During the conference, phones must be silent.
   FOR = durasi: I've worked here for 5 years.
   SINCE = sejak: She has been the manager since 2020.
   BY = paling lambat: Please send it by 5 PM.
   UNTIL/TILL = sampai: We worked until midnight.
   WITHIN = dalam kurun: Please respond within 24 hours.

─────────────────────────────────────────────
PREPOSISI TEMPAT
─────────────────────────────────────────────
AT = di titik/lokasi spesifik:
   at the office, at the meeting room, at reception, at the desk

ON = di permukaan:
   on the table, on the screen, on the wall, on the first floor, on page 5

IN = di dalam ruang:
   in the office, in the building, in the meeting room, in the cloud

Lainnya:
   UNDER/BELOW = di bawah: under the desk, below the minimum requirement
   ABOVE/OVER = di atas: above the budget, over the limit
   BETWEEN = di antara (dua): between the manager and the developer
   AMONG = di antara (banyak): among the staff members
   NEXT TO = di sebelah: next to the server room
   OPPOSITE = di seberang: opposite the reception desk
   NEAR = dekat: near the exit

─────────────────────────────────────────────
PREPOSISI LAIN YANG SERING DI TOEIC
─────────────────────────────────────────────
ABOUT = tentang: a report about the project
WITH = dengan: I work with a great team.
WITHOUT = tanpa: without proper authorization
FOR = untuk: responsible for the database
BY = oleh (passive)/dengan cara: written by the manager / by email
DESPITE / IN SPITE OF = meskipun: Despite the setback, the project continued.
BECAUSE OF / DUE TO = karena: due to technical issues
ACCORDING TO = menurut: According to the report, sales increased.

