─────────────────────────────────────────────
IMPERATIVE (Perintah)
─────────────────────────────────────────────
Rumus: V1 (langsung verb) + ...
   → Tidak ada subjek yang tertulis, karena subjeknya "you" tersirat

   Positif:
   Save the file before closing.
   Click the Submit button.
   Restart the computer.
   Update your password regularly.
   Attend the mandatory training session.

   Negatif:
   Don't share your password.
   Do not open unknown email attachments.
   Never delete files without backing them up first.

─────────────────────────────────────────────
POLITE REQUEST (Permintaan Sopan)
─────────────────────────────────────────────
Digunakan dalam konteks profesional dan bisnis:

Could you + V1?           (sopan, formal)
   Could you send me the updated report?

Would you + V1?           (sangat sopan)
   Would you review this document?

Would you mind + V-ing?   (sangat sopan — ingat: pakai -ing setelahnya!)
   Would you mind checking the server logs?
   ❌ Would you mind to check? (SALAH — jangan pakai to + V)

Can you + V1?             (informal/netral)
   Can you help me fix this bug?

Please + V1               (bisa sangat sopan atau formal)
   Please confirm your attendance.
   Please find the attached document.

I'd like you to + V1      (formal)
   I'd like you to present the findings tomorrow.

─────────────────────────────────────────────
OFFERS (Penawaran)
─────────────────────────────────────────────
   Would you like + noun?
      Would you like a copy of the report?

   Would you like to + V1?
      Would you like to join the call?

   Can I + V1?
      Can I help you with the setup?

   Shall I + V1?
      Shall I book the conference room?

