MATERI 12: PRESENT CONTINUOUS TENSE
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Prasyarat: Materi 3, 5
Kaitan TOEIC: Part 1 Listening (foto), Part 5

Rumus: Subject + To Be (am/is/are) + V-ing

KAPAN DIGUNAKAN:
   1. Aksi yang sedang berlangsung SEKARANG
      She is presenting the project. (sekarang sedang presentasi)
      The server is running an update. (sedang update)

   2. Rencana yang sudah pasti di masa depan
      We are meeting with the client tomorrow.
      She is flying to Singapore next week.

   3. Tren yang sedang terjadi
      More companies are adopting cloud technology.
      Remote work is becoming more common.

ATURAN EJAAN V-ING:
   a) Kebanyakan: tambah -ing → work → working, send → sending
   b) Verb berakhiran -e: hapus -e lalu tambah -ing → write → writing, code → coding
   c) CVC pendek: gandakan konsonan → run → running, sit → sitting, get → getting
   d) Berakhiran -ie: ganti -ie dengan -y lalu tambah -ing → die → dying, lie → lying

─────────────────────────────────────────────
STATIVE VERBS — TIDAK PAKAI -ING!
─────────────────────────────────────────────
Ini adalah JEBAKAN paling terkenal. Verba-verba berikut TIDAK BOLEH dipakai dalam bentuk continuous:

Perasaan/emosi: love, hate, like, prefer, want, need, wish
Pikiran/mental: know, understand, believe, remember, forget, realize, think (=berpendapat), mean
Kepemilikan: have (=memiliki), own, belong, possess
Persepsi: see, hear, smell, taste, feel (=merasakan)
Keadaan: seem, appear, look (=tampak), contain, consist, include

TOEIC TRAP:
   ❌ I am knowing the answer.
   ✅ I know the answer.

   ❌ She is having a new laptop.
   ✅ She has a new laptop. ("have" dalam arti memiliki)

   ❌ He is understanding the concept.
   ✅ He understands the concept.

PENGECUALIAN:
   Beberapa verba BOLEH pakai -ing tapi artinya berbeda:
   - "think" (sedang berpikir) vs "think" (berpendapat)
     I am thinking about the solution. (sedang memikirkan)
     I think it's a good idea. (saya berpendapat)
   - "have" (sedang melakukan) vs "have" (memiliki)
     She is having a meeting. (sedang mengadakan meeting)
     She has a laptop. (memiliki laptop)

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
MATERI 13: FUTURE SYSTEM
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Prasyarat: Materi 12, 5
Kaitan TOEIC: Soal tentang rencana perjalanan, jadwal bisnis

─────────────────────────────────────────────
WILL + V1 (keputusan spontan, janji, prediksi umum)
─────────────────────────────────────────────
   The server is overloaded. I'll restart it now. (keputusan spontan)
   I promise I will send the report by 5 PM. (janji)
   I think the project will be successful. (prediksi)
   Don't worry, I'll help you. (menawarkan bantuan)

─────────────────────────────────────────────
GOING TO + V1 (rencana terencana, prediksi berbasis bukti)
─────────────────────────────────────────────
   I am going to present the findings tomorrow. (sudah direncanakan)
   Look at those error logs — the server is going to crash. (bukti ada)
   They are going to hire three new developers. (sudah direncanakan)

─────────────────────────────────────────────
PRESENT CONTINUOUS sebagai FUTURE (rencana pasti)
─────────────────────────────────────────────
   I am meeting the client at 3 PM tomorrow.
   She is flying to Japan next week. (sudah ada tiket, reservasi)
   We are launching the app on Friday. (sudah dijadwalkan pasti)

─────────────────────────────────────────────
PRESENT SIMPLE sebagai FUTURE (jadwal resmi)
─────────────────────────────────────────────
   The train leaves at 7 AM tomorrow.
   The conference starts next Monday.
   The office closes at 6 PM.

PERBANDINGAN WILL vs GOING TO:
   Situasi: Kamu baru sadar ada meeting besok.
   → Will: "I will prepare the slides." (keputusan baru)

   Situasi: Sejak seminggu lalu kamu sudah plan presentasi.
   → Going to: "I am going to present the slides." (rencana lama)

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
MATERI 14: MODAL VERBS (Kata Kerja Modal)
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Prasyarat: Materi 2
Kaitan TOEIC: Sangat sering di Part 5 & 6

RUMUS DASAR: Modal + V1 (base form) — TIDAK ADA -s, -ing, -ed setelah modal!

─────────────────────────────────────────────
KEMAMPUAN (Ability)
─────────────────────────────────────────────
CAN = bisa (sekarang)
   I can fix this error.
   She can speak three languages.
   The system can handle 10,000 users simultaneously.

COULD = bisa (masa lalu / lebih sopan / kondisional)
   He could solve any problem. (masa lalu)
   Could you send me the file? (lebih sopan dari "can")

BE ABLE TO = mampu (lebih formal, bisa semua tense)
   I wasn't able to attend the meeting yesterday.
   She will be able to finish by tomorrow.

─────────────────────────────────────────────
KEHARUSAN / KEWAJIBAN (Necessity)
─────────────────────────────────────────────
MUST = harus (kewajiban dari diri sendiri/aturan kuat)
   You must submit the form by end of day.
   All employees must wear their ID.

HAVE TO = harus (kewajiban dari luar, situasi)
   I have to attend the training — it's mandatory.
   She had to rewrite the entire code. (bisa past tense)

SHOULD = seharusnya (saran, rekomendasi)
   You should back up your files regularly.
   The manager should address this issue immediately.

NEED TO = perlu
   We need to upgrade the server.
   You don't need to come in on Saturday. (tidak perlu)

OUGHT TO = seharusnya (lebih formal dari should)
   Employees ought to follow the company policy.

─────────────────────────────────────────────
LARANGAN (Prohibition)
─────────────────────────────────────────────
MUST NOT / MUSTN'T = dilarang keras
   You must not share confidential information.
   Employees must not use personal devices for work.

CANNOT / CAN'T = tidak boleh
   You cannot access this file without permission.

SHOULD NOT / SHOULDN'T = sebaiknya tidak
   You shouldn't ignore security updates.

─────────────────────────────────────────────
KEMUNGKINAN (Possibility)
─────────────────────────────────────────────
MAY = mungkin (50-60% kemungkinan, formal)
   The project may be delayed.
   She may not attend the meeting.

MIGHT = mungkin (lebih kecil kemungkinannya, ~40%)
   The server might crash if we don't upgrade.
   He might have the password.

COULD = bisa jadi (kemungkinan)
   There could be a problem with the network.

─────────────────────────────────────────────
TOEIC TRAPS — MODAL
─────────────────────────────────────────────
❌ She must to attend the meeting.
✅ She must attend the meeting. (tidak ada "to" setelah modal)

❌ He can speaks English fluently.
✅ He can speak English fluently. (tidak ada -s setelah modal)

❌ They should to update the software.
✅ They should update the software.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
MATERI 15: COMPARISON (Perbandingan)
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Prasyarat: Materi 1 (Adjective, Adverb)

─────────────────────────────────────────────
COMPARATIVE (Perbandingan antara 2 hal) — lebih dari
─────────────────────────────────────────────
Adjective pendek (1-2 suku kata): + -er
   fast → faster, small → smaller, cheap → cheaper
   big → bigger (CVC: gandakan konsonan)
   easy → easier (y → ier)

Adjective panjang (3+ suku kata): more + adjective
   more efficient, more expensive, more reliable, more professional

Rumus: ... + adjective-er/more + adjective + THAN + ...
   This laptop is faster than my old one.
   Cloud storage is more efficient than physical servers.
   The new version is more reliable than the previous one.

─────────────────────────────────────────────
SUPERLATIVE (Yang paling di antara semua)
─────────────────────────────────────────────
Adjective pendek: the + adjective-est
   the fastest, the smallest, the cheapest

Adjective panjang: the most + adjective
   the most efficient, the most expensive, the most reliable

Contoh:
   This is the fastest server we have ever used.
   She is the most experienced developer on the team.
   It is the most expensive option, but also the most reliable.

─────────────────────────────────────────────
EQUALITY (Sama dengan)
─────────────────────────────────────────────
   as + adjective + as = sama seperti
   This tablet is as fast as that laptop.
   The new employee is as productive as the senior staff.

   not as + adjective + as = tidak se...
   The free version is not as reliable as the premium version.

─────────────────────────────────────────────
BENTUK TIDAK BERATURAN
─────────────────────────────────────────────
good → better → best
bad → worse → worst
much/many → more → most
little → less → least
far → farther/further → farthest/furthest

Contoh:
   This solution is better than what we had before.
   The worst-case scenario is a complete system failure.
   We need more resources to complete this project.

