━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
MATERI 17: PERFECT TENSES
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Prasyarat: Materi 5, 7, 3
Kaitan TOEIC: Sangat sering di Part 5 & 6

─────────────────────────────────────────────
PRESENT PERFECT: have/has + V3
─────────────────────────────────────────────
KAPAN: Kejadian di masa lalu yang RELEVAN DENGAN SEKARANG
(tidak ada waktu spesifik, atau dampaknya terasa sekarang)

Signal words: already, yet, just, ever, never, since, for, recently, so far, up to now

   The team has already finished the testing phase.
   She has worked here for five years.
   Have you ever used this software before?
   I haven't received your email yet.
   They have just released the new update.

BEDAKAN PRESENT PERFECT vs SIMPLE PAST:
   Simple Past: I sent the report yesterday. (ada waktu spesifik: yesterday)
   Present Perfect: I have sent the report. (sudah dikirim, relevan sekarang, tidak ada waktu spesifik)

   Simple Past: She worked at Google in 2019. (sudah selesai, waktu spesifik)
   Present Perfect: She has worked at Google. (pengalaman yang dia punya)

SINCE vs FOR:
   SINCE = titik waktu awal: since 2020, since Monday, since last year
   FOR = durasi: for 3 years, for two weeks, for a long time

   She has been the manager since 2021.
   He has worked here for 6 months.

─────────────────────────────────────────────
PAST PERFECT: had + V3
─────────────────────────────────────────────
KAPAN: Kejadian yang terjadi SEBELUM kejadian lain di masa lalu

Signal words: before, after, when, by the time, already, just

   By the time the manager arrived, the team had already finished the meeting.
   She had submitted the report before the deadline.
   When I called him, he had left the office.
   They couldn't access the system because the password had expired.

LOGIKA:
   Kejadian 1 (lebih dulu) → Past Perfect (had + V3)
   Kejadian 2 (terjadi setelah) → Simple Past

   "The server crashed because someone had deleted the configuration file."
   (pertama: hapus file konfigurasi → kemudian: server crash)

─────────────────────────────────────────────
FUTURE PERFECT: will have + V3
─────────────────────────────────────────────
KAPAN: Kejadian yang AKAN SELESAI sebelum titik waktu di masa depan

   By the end of this week, we will have completed the project.
   She will have finished the training by next Monday.
   By the time you arrive, I will have prepared everything.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
MATERI 18: PASSIVE VOICE (Kalimat Pasif)
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Prasyarat: Materi 3, semua tense, V3
Kaitan TOEIC: SANGAT SERING — hampir selalu ada

KONSEP DASAR:
   Active: Someone does something.
      The developer fixed the bug. (developer = pelaku, bug = yang terkena)
   
   Passive: Something is done (by someone).
      The bug was fixed (by the developer). (bug jadi subjek, pelaku sering tidak disebutkan)

KAPAN DIGUNAKAN PASSIVE:
   1. Pelaku tidak diketahui atau tidak penting: The files were deleted.
   2. Pelaku sudah jelas dari konteks: The report has been submitted.
   3. Konteks formal/resmi: Employees are required to wear ID.
   4. Fokus pada objek/hasil, bukan pelaku: The contract was signed yesterday.

RUMUS: To Be (sesuai tense) + V3

TABEL PASSIVE VOICE LENGKAP:

Tense               | Active                      | Passive
Simple Present      | She sends emails.           | Emails are sent.
Simple Past         | He wrote the report.        | The report was written.
Present Continuous  | She is writing the report.  | The report is being written.
Past Continuous     | He was fixing the bug.      | The bug was being fixed.
Present Perfect     | They have approved it.      | It has been approved.
Past Perfect        | She had submitted it.       | It had been submitted.
Future (will)       | They will send the invoice. | The invoice will be sent.
Modal               | You must submit the form.   | The form must be submitted.

Contoh kalimat bisnis:
   The project was completed on time. (simple past passive)
   The meeting has been postponed until further notice. (present perfect passive)
   New employees will be trained next month. (future passive)
   All data must be backed up regularly. (modal passive)
   The contract is being reviewed by the legal team. (present continuous passive)
   The annual report will have been published by December. (future perfect passive)

BY-PHRASE:
   Sertakan BY + pelaku hanya jika pelakunya penting:
   The software was developed by a team of 20 engineers. (penting untuk disebutkan)
   The email was sent. (siapa yang kirim tidak perlu disebutkan)

TOEIC TRAPS — PASSIVE:
   ❌ The report was write yesterday.
   ✅ The report was written yesterday. (harus V3)

   ❌ The bug has been fix.
   ✅ The bug has been fixed. (harus V3)

   ❌ The files are been deleted.
   ✅ The files are being deleted. (present continuous passive = are + being + V3)

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
MATERI 19: GERUND & INFINITIVE
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Prasyarat: Materi 1, 14
Kaitan TOEIC: Part 5 verb form trap — SANGAT SERING KELUAR

Gerund = V + -ing yang berfungsi sebagai noun
Infinitive = to + V1

─────────────────────────────────────────────
VERBS YANG DIIKUTI GERUND (-ing)
─────────────────────────────────────────────
Hafal dengan cerita: "Mereka MENIKMATI MENGHINDARI SARAN"
   enjoy, avoid, suggest, mind, keep, finish, consider, practice, deny, delay, admit, risk

   I enjoy working on challenging projects.
   He finished coding the application.
   She avoided making errors by testing thoroughly.
   They suggested using cloud storage.
   Would you mind sending me the file?
   We considered upgrading the server.

─────────────────────────────────────────────
VERBS YANG DIIKUTI INFINITIVE (to + V)
─────────────────────────────────────────────
Hafal dengan cerita: "Mereka MEMUTUSKAN BERENCANA BERHARAP"
   want, need, decide, plan, hope, expect, agree, refuse, offer, manage, promise, fail, tend

   She decided to change her career path.
   They plan to launch the product next quarter.
   He agreed to extend the deadline.
   We hope to receive your response soon.
   She managed to fix the critical bug.
   I need to update my skills.

─────────────────────────────────────────────
VERBS YANG DIIKUTI KEDUANYA (tapi MAKNANYA BERBEDA!)
─────────────────────────────────────────────
Ini adalah TOEIC TRAP yang sangat sering keluar!

REMEMBER:
   remember + gerund = ingat (kejadian masa lalu)
      I remember attending that conference. (ingat pernah hadir)
   
   remember + infinitive = ingat (untuk melakukan sesuatu)
      Please remember to save your work. (ingat untuk menyimpan)

FORGET:
   forget + gerund = lupa (kejadian masa lalu)
      I'll never forget working on that project. (tidak akan lupa pengalaman itu)
   
   forget + infinitive = lupa (untuk melakukan sesuatu)
      Don't forget to send the report. (jangan lupa mengirim)

STOP:
   stop + gerund = berhenti melakukan sesuatu
      She stopped working at 6 PM. (berhenti bekerja)
   
   stop + infinitive = berhenti untuk melakukan sesuatu lain
      He stopped to check his phone. (berhenti [dari aktivitas lain] untuk cek HP)

TRY:
   try + gerund = mencoba (eksperimen)
      Try restarting the computer. (coba restart, lihat hasilnya)
   
   try + infinitive = berusaha keras (ada kesulitan)
      She tried to fix the bug but couldn't. (berusaha memperbaiki tapi tidak bisa)

─────────────────────────────────────────────
GERUND SETELAH PREPOSISI
─────────────────────────────────────────────
Setelah PREPOSISI, selalu gunakan GERUND (bukan infinitive):

   interested in + V-ing: She is interested in learning new technologies.
   responsible for + V-ing: He is responsible for managing the database.
   good at + V-ing: She is good at debugging code.
   afraid of + V-ing: He is afraid of making mistakes.
   instead of + V-ing: Use this method instead of rewriting the code.
   before/after + V-ing: Always backup before updating the system.
   without + V-ing: Don't submit without proofreading.
   thank you for + V-ing: Thank you for attending the meeting.

