MATERI 20: RELATIVE CLAUSES (Klausa Relatif)
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Prasyarat: Materi 2, 4
Kaitan TOEIC: Part 5 & 6 complex sentences

FUNGSI: Menerangkan noun (seperti adjective, tapi berupa klausa)

─────────────────────────────────────────────
RELATIVE PRONOUNS
─────────────────────────────────────────────
WHO = untuk orang (sebagai subjek klausa)
   The developer who fixed the bug is very talented.
   The manager who runs this department has 10 years of experience.

WHOM = untuk orang (sebagai objek klausa — lebih formal)
   The client whom we met yesterday was impressed.
   The employee whom the manager recommended got promoted.

WHICH = untuk benda/hewan
   The software which we use is very efficient.
   The report which she submitted contained errors.

THAT = untuk orang atau benda (defining only)
   The file that you sent is corrupt.
   The programmer that built this app is a genius.

WHOSE = kepemilikan
   The employee whose computer crashed had to borrow another one.
   The company whose headquarters is in Jakarta is our client.

WHERE = untuk tempat
   The office where I work is in South Jakarta.
   The server room where all data is stored is secure.

WHEN = untuk waktu
   The day when the system crashed was a Monday.
   Do you remember the time when we launched the first version?

─────────────────────────────────────────────
DEFINING vs NON-DEFINING
─────────────────────────────────────────────
DEFINING (tanpa koma) = informasi penting, tanpa itu kalimat tidak jelas
   The employee that submitted the report on time will be rewarded.
   (kita perlu tahu "which employee" → defining)

NON-DEFINING (dengan koma) = informasi tambahan, kalimat masih jelas tanpanya
   Mr. Reza, who is our IT manager, will lead the training.
   (kita sudah tahu siapa Mr. Reza → koma → non-defining)
   Note: THAT tidak bisa digunakan dalam non-defining clause

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
MATERI 21: CONJUNCTIONS (Kata Penghubung — Deep Study)
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Prasyarat: Materi 2
Kaitan TOEIC: Part 5 conjunction trap sangat sering!

─────────────────────────────────────────────
COORDINATING CONJUNCTIONS: FANBOYS
─────────────────────────────────────────────
F = For (karena/sebab — formal)
A = And (dan)
N = Nor (dan juga tidak)
B = But (tapi)
O = Or (atau)
Y = Yet (namun/tapi — lebih formal dari but)
S = So (jadi/sehingga)

   She works hard, and she always meets her deadlines.
   The design is simple, but it is very effective.
   We can use Cloud A or Cloud B.
   He didn't attend the meeting, nor did he send an email.
   The deadline is tight, yet the team is confident.
   The server was overloaded, so we upgraded it.

─────────────────────────────────────────────
SUBORDINATING CONJUNCTIONS (Adverb Clauses)
─────────────────────────────────────────────
CONTRAST (Meskipun/Walaupun):
   although / even though / though + clause (diikuti kalimat)
      Although the system is old, it still works well.
      Even though there was a problem, the project was delivered on time.

   despite / in spite of + noun/gerund (diikuti kata benda atau gerund, BUKAN kalimat)
      Despite the technical issues, the launch was successful.
      In spite of having limited resources, they completed the project.

   TOEIC TRAP:
   ❌ Despite the system is old, it works.
   ✅ Despite the system being old, it works. (atau: Although the system is old, it works.)

   however / nevertheless / nonetheless = menunjukkan kontras (biasanya di awal kalimat baru)
      The budget was limited. However, the project was completed successfully.

CAUSE (Karena):
   because + clause: She succeeded because she worked hard.
   since / as + clause (lebih formal): Since the deadline is tomorrow, we need to hurry.
   due to / because of + noun/gerund: The delay was due to a technical failure.

   TOEIC TRAP:
   ❌ Because of the server crashed...
   ✅ Because the server crashed... (because + clause)
   ✅ Because of the server crash... (because of + noun)

PURPOSE (Tujuan):
   so that + clause: We upgraded the server so that it could handle more traffic.
   in order to + V1: She studied hard in order to pass the TOEIC test.
   to + V1 (paling singkat): He attended the seminar to learn new skills.

CONDITION (Syarat):
   if: If you restart the server, it should work.
   unless = if not: Unless you update the software, it won't work properly.
   provided that / as long as: As long as you follow the steps, you'll be fine.

TIME (Waktu):
   when: When the meeting starts, please be silent.
   while: While I was coding, she was testing.
   before: Back up your data before you update.
   after: After you finish, please send the report.
   until: Wait until the download is complete.
   as soon as: As soon as I receive your email, I'll reply.
   by the time: By the time he arrived, the meeting had ended.

RESULT (Hasil):
   so + adjective/adverb + that: The system is so slow that it takes 10 minutes to load.
   such + noun + that: It was such a serious bug that we had to halt the release.

─────────────────────────────────────────────
CORRELATIVE CONJUNCTIONS (Berpasangan)
─────────────────────────────────────────────
both...and = baik...maupun
   She is both a developer and a designer.

either...or = salah satu dari... atau...
   Either you fix the bug, or we cancel the release.

neither...nor = tidak...maupun tidak
   The system is neither fast nor reliable.

not only...but also = tidak hanya...tetapi juga
   She not only codes well but also communicates effectively.

