MATERI 28: SUBJECT-VERB AGREEMENT
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Kaitan TOEIC: SANGAT SERING, paling banyak diuji di Part 5

ATURAN DASAR:
   Subjek SINGULAR → Verb + s/es (is, was, has)
   Subjek PLURAL → Verb tanpa -s (are, were, have)

─────────────────────────────────────────────
JEBAKAN YANG PALING SERING KELUAR:
─────────────────────────────────────────────
1. Indefinite Pronoun = SELALU SINGULAR
   everyone, someone, anyone, no one, nobody, nothing, something, everything, each, either, neither
   
   Everyone has to submit the form by Friday. (✓ has, bukan have)
   Neither option seems suitable. (✓ seems)
   Each employee is required to wear an ID. (✓ is)

2. Collective Noun — BISA SINGULAR atau PLURAL tergantung konteks
   the team, the committee, the staff, the company, the board, the group
   
   American English: biasanya singular
   The team is working on the new feature.
   
   British English: bisa plural
   The team are working on the new feature.

3. Either/Neither...Or/Nor — Agreement dengan NOUN TERDEKAT
   Either the manager or the employees are responsible. (employees → are)
   Neither the employees nor the manager is available. (manager → is)

4. Inverted Sentence (There is/are)
   There is a problem with the network. (a problem = singular → is)
   There are several issues to address. (several issues = plural → are)

5. Relative Clause Agreement
   The file that is corrupted needs to be deleted. (file = singular → is)
   The files that are corrupted need to be deleted. (files = plural → are)

6. Expressions of Quantity
   a number of + plural noun → PLURAL verb
      A number of employees are absent today.
   
   the number of + plural noun → SINGULAR verb
      The number of employees has increased.
   
   a lot of / plenty of → tergantung noun-nya
      A lot of work needs to be done. (work = uncountable → singular)
      A lot of employees have signed up. (employees = plural → plural)

7. Gerund as Subject = SINGULAR
   Coding complex algorithms takes time. (takes, bukan take)
   Attending meetings is mandatory. (is, bukan are)

8. With/Along with/As well as/Together with — TIDAK mengubah subjek
   The manager, along with his team, is attending the conference. (manager → is)
   The CEO, as well as the directors, was present at the meeting. (CEO → was)

