MATERI 34: COMMON TOEIC TRAPS (Jebakan TOEIC yang Paling Sering)
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

─────────────────────────────────────────────
CONFUSABLE WORDS (Kata yang Sering Tertukar)
─────────────────────────────────────────────
affect vs effect:
   AFFECT = verb (mempengaruhi): The bug affected the system performance.
   EFFECT = noun (dampak/hasil): The effect of the update was significant.
   "to have an effect ON" = memiliki dampak pada

raise vs rise:
   RAISE = verb transitif (menaikkan — butuh objek): They raised the salary.
   RISE = verb intransitif (naik — tidak butuh objek): Sales rose by 20%.

lay vs lie:
   LAY = verb transitif (meletakkan): Please lay the documents on the table.
   LIE = verb intransitif (berbaring/terletak): The files lie on the server.

accept vs except:
   ACCEPT = verb (menerima): I accept your proposal.
   EXCEPT = preposition (kecuali): Everyone attended except the manager.

advice vs advise:
   ADVICE = noun (saran): She gave me good advice.
   ADVISE = verb (menyarankan): She advised me to apply for the position.

between vs among:
   BETWEEN = di antara (2 hal): The agreement is between the two companies.
   AMONG = di antara (lebih dari 2): She is popular among her colleagues.

its vs it's:
   its = possessive (milik): The company launched its new product.
   it's = it is: It's time to start the meeting.

there vs their vs they're:
   there = tempat/there is/are: There is a meeting today.
   their = possessive (milik mereka): Their project was successful.
   they're = they are: They're working on a new feature.

then vs than:
   then = kemudian (waktu): Finish the task, then submit it.
   than = perbandingan: This version is better than the previous one.

further vs farther:
   farther = jarak fisik: The office is farther than I thought.
   further = lebih lanjut (metaforis): We need to discuss this further.

─────────────────────────────────────────────
GRAMMATICAL TRAPS:
─────────────────────────────────────────────
DOUBLE NEGATIVE (tidak boleh ada dua negatif dalam satu klausa):
   ❌ We don't have no solutions.
   ✅ We don't have any solutions. / We have no solutions.

EXTRA SUBJECT (pronoun berlebih):
   ❌ The manager, he called the meeting.
   ✅ The manager called the meeting.

MISSING SUBJECT:
   ❌ Is important to back up your data.
   ✅ It is important to back up your data.

WRONG TENSE:
   ❌ She has submitted the report yesterday. (ada yesterday → Simple Past)
   ✅ She submitted the report yesterday.

   ❌ He works here since 2020. (since → Present Perfect)
   ✅ He has worked here since 2020.

PREPOSITION ERROR:
   ❌ We discussed about the issue. (discuss tidak butuh preposition)
   ✅ We discussed the issue.

   ❌ Please contact with me. (contact tidak butuh preposition)
   ✅ Please contact me.

